Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.24,0:21:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,minority. Forget it. You've juiced it.\NSo sooner or later, you got to give up
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.88,0:21:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the juicing of it, of having been\Nwronged, whatever it may be,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.52,0:21:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,being dumb and ugly. You know what I\Nmean? You got to quit juicing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.20,0:22:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?\NIt's unconsciously we get satisfaction
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.48,0:22:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and that satisfaction is what you have\Nto be willing to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.55,0:22:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So it's always the same thing. It's it's\Nit isn't multiple things you have to let
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.28,0:22:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,go of. It's only one thing that one is\Nderiving satisfaction
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.15,0:22:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,out of that positionality.\NPositionality being wrong, being
